                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17770115-1-victim48 t17770115-1-viclabel3"></join>, the corner of <placeName id="t17770115-1-crimeloc4">Suffolk-street, Charing-cross</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17770115-1-crimeloc4" type="placeName" value="Suffolk-street, Charing-cross"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17770115-1-crimeloc4" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17770115-1-off1 t17770115-1-crimeloc4"></join>: upon the 6th of December, between eight and nine o'clock in the morning, I opened the case and missed a pair of buckles; my master came into the shop and missed two more; on examination we found a piece of the glass broke out; I had seen them at three o'clock the preceding day.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177701150003"></xptr>[ Two pair were produced in court by Grubb the constable, and one pair by 
               <persName id="t17770115-1-person51">
                  Lloyd
